 Fix Strategies\n\n### Strategy 1: Install Missing Dependencies\nAdd the following packages to the Dockerfile or build script:\n```bash\napt-get install -y libbrotli-dev libwebp-dev libbz2-dev\n```\n\n### Strategy 2: Check Library Search Paths\nEnsure linker can find the libraries:\n```bash\n# Check if libraries exist\nfind /usr -name \"libbrotlidec*\" 2>/dev/null\nfind /usr -name \"libsharpyuv*\" 2>/dev/null\nfind /usr -name \"libbz2*\" 2>/dev/null\n\n# Add library paths if needed\nexport LD_LIBRARY_PATH=/usr/local/lib:$LD_LIBRARY_PATH\n```\n\n### Strategy 3: Modify Build Configuration\nCheck GDAL's CMake configuration for library detection:\n```bash\n# Check CMakeCache.txt for library paths\ngrep -i \"brotli\\|sharpyuv\\|bz2\" /path/to/build/CMakeCache.txt\n```\n\n### Strategy 4: Update Build Script\nModify `/src/gdal/fuzzers/build.sh` to install missing dependencies:\n```bash\n# Add before the build commands\napt-get update && apt-get install -y libbrotli-dev libwebp-dev libbz2-dev\n```\n\n## Common Patterns in OSS-Fuzz Builds\n\n1. **Missing system dependencies**: Often need to install -dev packages\n2. **Linker path issues**: Libraries installed but not in standard paths\n3. **Version mismatches**: Installed libraries may be wrong version\n4. **Build script omissions**: Dependencies not listed in build script\n\n## Priority Recommendations\n\n1. **HIGH**: Install missing packages via apt-get\n2. **MEDIUM**: Check CMake configuration for library detection\n3. **LOW**: Verify library symlinks and paths\n\n## Expected Outcome\n\nAfter installing the missing dependencies, the build should progress to the next stage. The fact that GDAL compiled successfully indicates the core build system is working correctly."})
